118
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,280
She is the daughter of Minister Liu,
who was once engaged to you.

119
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,400
Sir, how much is this flower lantern?

120
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,240
You really have a good eye.

121
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:54,360
That is a prize for the festival.
It's not for sale.

122
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,040
Just guess the lantern riddle to win it.

123
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,160
The lantern riddle?

124
00:09:00,503 --> 00:09:04,689
♪Filling the expectation
of many years' vacancy♪

125
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:07,120
Excuse me. Thank you.

126
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,120
Mr. Yu? Isn't this Mr. Yu?

127
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,600
Yes.

128
00:09:16,183 --> 00:09:20,496
♪Through blurred sadness,
I can see the clear future♪

129
00:09:20,496 --> 00:09:27,168
♪You're still in my heart♪

130
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,960
(He is...?)

131
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,360
(Son of Assistant Minister of Rites, Yu Minghe)
That's the son of Assistant Minister Yu.

132
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,400
He's well-read.

133
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,200
(The son of Mr. Yu.)

134
00:09:35,855 --> 00:09:38,302
(I remember Pei's evaluation of him.)

135
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:41,312
Yu Minghe, a do-nothing.

136
00:09:42,799 --> 00:09:43,857
Unfit for significant tasks.

137
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:49,120
(That is good. Low-key and safe.)

138
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,600
Sir, why did you stop writing?

139
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:08,560
One more question
and you can win the first place.

140
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:11,240
I'm just doing this for fun, not to win.

141
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:16,040
The first place can be left for someone
who truly wants to win.

142
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,880
(Gentle with restraint.)

143
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,680
(What is most commendable
is that he is low-key and humble.)

144
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,520
(He's a very safe choice.)

145
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:29,000
Would you mind writing
a poem now as a memento?

146
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,720
You can choose whatever prize
you want from the shop.

147
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,040
Could I give this lantern
to this young lady?

148
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,160
Of course, you can.

149
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,800
Thank you. I'm not going
to take your lantern for nothing.

150
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,840
You give me the lantern,
and we compose a poem together, okay?

151
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:55,200
That'll be a romantic story.

152
00:11:01,045 --> 00:11:03,304
(In the crowd once and again,
I look for her in vain.)

153
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:13,184
(Perchance I turn, there they are in the dimming light.)
What a nice poem!

154
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:34,640
Please spare me.

155
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,280
Whose child is this?

156
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,320
Please spare me.

157
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,440
(It's her.)

158
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,480
Your Highness.

159
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:48,760
(It's Pei Xun.)

160
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,000
What's wrong?

161
00:11:52,608 --> 00:11:53,840
Let's go.

162
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:56,160
Why are they leaving?
They haven't finished the game yet.

163
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,560
(How could it be her?)

164
00:12:00,378 --> 00:12:04,035
♪Time has taken away all
between you and me♪

165
00:12:04,035 --> 00:12:06,147
♪Yet memories surreptitiously remain♪

166
00:12:06,147 --> 00:12:08,800
♪The thrill of encountering you again♪

167
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:12,192
♪Is but an exchange of glances
in a split second♪

168
00:12:12,544 --> 00:12:16,544
♪The stars that light up the night
scattered around us♪

169
00:12:16,544 --> 00:12:20,995
♪So-called worries become
an excuse to evade♪

170
00:12:20,995 --> 00:12:23,494
♪Not daring to look back again♪

171
00:12:23,936 --> 00:12:28,448
♪Your tenderness is always behind me♪

172
